    "comment": "Rationale: CPEB4 is detected in the PSD fraction from IP from hippocampal neurons 21 DIV. Adittionally, CPEB4 immunofluorescence seems to be enriched in areas juxtaposed to synaptophysin-positive pre-synapses (primary rat hippocampal neurons as decribed in Huang et al., 2002).\n\n24/9/2017 Pim\n- Literal: \"Finally, both CPEB3 and CPEB4, when fused to GFP, were detected in dendrites, often as puncta (Figure 5C)\"\n- Literal: \"Taken together, these data show that CPEB3 and CPEB4 are expressed in only partially overlapping regions of the brain; within hippocampal neurons, where both are expressed, they appear to be synaptic.\"\n- The mRNA translation data is too poorly shown in this paper lacking clear synaptic relevance although looking at AMPAR translation.. Experimental description: 24/9/2017 Pim\n- Information on tissues and OE constructs used in Fig.5 are not stated by the authors. Authors contacted in email dd. 24/9/2017 (Joel.Richter@umassmed.edu). Answer:\n\n\"rat\" cultured neurons.\nGFP-hCPEB3 and GFP-hCPEB4 (human).\nThank, Yi-Shuian\n- Rat species was selected based on the localization in the PSD fraction.",
